excerpt: Built in 1895, restored home of famous businessman Tjong A Fie, offering a gallery & guided tours.
detail_description: Tjong A Fie Mansion, built in 1895, is the restored home of the renowned businessman Tjong A Fie. It serves as a gallery and offers guided tours for visitors. The mansion stands as a historical landmark and museum, representing Medan's rich heritage. Despite Medan's European plantation town appearance, Tjong A Fie, a Chinese immigrant, became its most famous resident through his remarkable rags-to-riches story.
name: Tjong A Fie Mansion
address: Jl. Jend. Ahmad Yani No.105, Kesawan, Medan Barat, Medan City, North Sumatra 20111, Indonesia

excerpt: Detailed displays of taxidermied animals in their natural habitats, plus a cafe & gift shop.
detail_description: If you're in Medan and looking for a unique experience, the Rahmat International Wildlife Museum & Gallery is a must-visit. This natural history museum boasts an extensive collection of over 5,000 stuffed animals representing around 2,500 species from various habitats. The displays are categorized according to habitat, offering visitors a chance to appreciate the diversity of wildlife worldwide. Owned by conservationist Rahmat Shah, the museum aims to inspire love and appreciation for nature.
name: Rahmat International Wildlife Museum & Gallery
address: Jl. S. Parman No.309, Petisah Hulu, Medan Baru, Medan City, North Sumatra 20152, Indonesia

excerpt: Built in 2005, this Indo-Mogul-style Catholic temple is dedicated to Our Lady of Good Health.
detail_description: Graha Bunda Maria Annai Velangkanni, also known as Lady of Good Health Church, is a unique Indo-Mogul-style Catholic temple located in Medan. Built in 2005, it is dedicated to Our Lady of Good Health and draws inspiration from the Velankanni Church in India. The shrine features stunning murals, sculptures, and stained glass windows that contribute to its serene ambiance.
name: Graha Bunda Maria Annai Velangkanni
address: Jl. Taman Sakura Indah Jl. Sakura III No.7-10, Tanjung Selamat, Medan Tuntungan, Medan City, North Sumatra 20135, Indonesia

excerpt: Small museum exploring local history & culture, with tribal artifacts & guided tours.
detail_description: The State Museum of North Sumatra offers a fascinating exploration of the region's history and culture. Visitors can embark on a visual journey through different periods, including the Muslim, Hindu, Buddhist, and Dutch colonial eras. The museum houses an impressive collection of tribal artifacts such as ancient weaponry, textiles, farming equipment, and carved wooden coffins. It provides well-documented exhibits in both English and Indonesian to offer insights into the rich heritage of the province.
name: State Museum of North Sumatra
address: Jl. HM. Joni No.51, West Teladan, Medan Kota, Medan City, North Sumatra 20217, Indonesia

excerpt: Indonesian food, coffee shops & global fare at a modern food court with indoor & outdoor seating.
detail_description: Merdeka Walk is a popular modern food court in Medan City, known for its diverse culinary offerings and vibrant atmosphere. It's a great spot for families to hang out, though it can get crowded, making parking a challenge. The place comes alive at night with beautiful lighting and offers a view of old architectural buildings while you dine. With its clean sidewalks and pick-up points for online vehicles, it's an ideal location to enjoy global cuisine and local delicacies with loved ones.
name: Merdeka Walk
address: HMRH+366, Jl. Balai Kota, Kesawan, Medan Barat, Medan City, North Sumatra 20231, Indonesia

excerpt: Large Buddhist temple complex featuring ornate Chinese architecture, gardens & a vegetarian cafe.
detail_description: Maha Vihara Maitreya is a significant Buddhist temple complex in Indonesia, boasting impressive Chinese architecture and serene gardens. It offers insight into Medan's religious background and traditions, making it a popular destination for those interested in Buddhism. The temple's ornate walls are adorned with intricate reliefs of mythical creatures, providing ample photo opportunities.
name: Maha Vihara Maitreya
address: Medan, Komplek Perumahan Cemara Asri Jl. Cemara Asri Boulevard Raya No.8, Percut Sei Tuan, Deli Serdang Regency, North Sumatra 20371, Indonesia

excerpt: Relaxed, enduring bakery & restaurant featuring Western & Asian dishes.
detail_description: Located across the street from Tjong A Fie Mansion, Tip Top Restaurant is a long-standing establishment in Medan, dating back to 1934. This iconic restaurant features colonial-style architecture and offers a diverse menu of Indonesian and international cuisine. In addition to savory dishes, visitors can indulge in delectable cakes from the in-house bakery or enjoy ice cream from the parlor.
name: Tip Top Restaurant
address: Jl. Jend. Ahmad Yani No.92 A-B No.92 A-B, Kesawan, Kec. Medan Bar., Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara 20212, Indonesia

detail_description: Masjid Raya Al-Mashun, also known as the Grand Mosque, is a significant tourist attraction in Medan. It holds historical and religious value, attracting many Muslim visitors due to its unique architectural style. The mosque's stunning exterior resembles a beautiful wedding cake and features Moorish and cathedral influences. Inside, it symbolizes the Muslim community and the essence of Islam in Medan.
name: Masjid Raya Al-Mashun
address: Jl. Mahkamah No.74c, RT.02, Mesjid, Kec. Medan Kota, Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara 20212, Indonesia

detail_description: Garuda Restaurant is a popular chain in Medan, offering quintessential local cuisine. Known for its Nasi Padang, which translates to Padang Rice, the restaurant brings over twenty dishes to each table for diners to choose from. The concept allows customers to pay only for the dishes they select. While the prices are relatively high and the lack of air conditioning can make it hot inside, the friendly staff and attentive service contribute to a positive dining experience.
name: Garuda Restaurant
address: Jl. Palang Merah No.26A, Kesawan, Medan Barat, Medan City, North Sumatra 20151, Indonesia

detail_description: UCOK DURIAN MEDAN is a renowned spot in Medan, drawing both locals and tourists to savor an array of durian types. The stall offers sweet, bitter, and buttery options, ensuring a delightful experience for durian enthusiasts. Visitors praise the quality of the fruit and commend the attentive service provided by the friendly staff. While some find it slightly pricey, many agree that it's a must-visit for anyone passionate about durian.
name: UCOK DURIAN MEDAN
address: Jl. K.H. Wahid Hasyim No.30-32, Babura, Kec. Medan Baru, Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara 20153, Indonesia

detail_description: Istana Maimun, located in Medan, was once the royal palace of the Sultanate of Deli. Today, it has been transformed into a museum, allowing visitors to explore its rich history and cultural significance. The museum showcases the opulent throne room and offers insights into the royal family's legacy through displays of ancient clothing and other intriguing artifacts.
name: Istana Maimun
address: A U R, Kec. Medan Maimun, Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara 20212, Indonesia

excerpt: Built in 1884, this place of worship to the Hindu goddess of rain has a colorful, ornate decor.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Indian quarter of Medan, the Mariamman Temple stands as a stunning testament to cultural diversity and architectural beauty. Established in 1884, this Hindu temple is dedicated to the goddess of rain and showcases an exquisite Dravidian style typical of South India. Visitors can wander through its colorful alleyways, marveling at intricate designs and ornate decorations that adorn its storied tower.
name: Mariamman Temple
address: Jl. Teuku Umar No.18, Petisah Tengah, Medan Petisah, Medan City, North Sumatra 20151, Indonesia

excerpt: Multilevel enclosed mall with an open, airy feel, contemporary food court & a movie theater.
detail_description: Sun Plaza is a modern and popular multilevel enclosed mall located in the heart of Medan city. It offers an open, airy feel with contemporary food court and a movie theater. The plaza is currently undergoing renovations to enhance its ambience while still operating as usual. It features a supermarket, department stores, cinema, F&B outlets, local and international fashion brands, banks, money changers, and ATM centers.
name: Sun Plaza
address: Jl. KH. Zainul Arifin No.7, Madras Hulu, Medan Polonia, Medan City, North Sumatra 20152, Indonesia

detail_description: Soto Kesawan is a must-visit spot in Medan for those seeking authentic local cuisine. This small, local warung has been serving up traditional flavorsome and creamy soto udang since 1950. The spicy coconut-based broth is filled with tender prawns and can be enjoyed with crumbly roti canai.
name: Soto Kesawan
address: HMMJ+X5C, JL. Ahmad Yani, Kesawan, Kec. Medan Bar., Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara 20231, Indonesia

detail_description: Medan Post Office, established in 1911 during the Dutch colonial period, stands as a prominent landmark in the heart of the city. Its traditional colonial architecture, featuring a distinctive dome and half-circle windows, showcases its historical significance. The building still operates as a functioning post office and also houses an impressive exhibit of stamp collections. Visitors can experience the charm of this architectural gem while exploring its postal services and historical displays.
name: Medan Post Office
address: Jl. Melati Raya No.10, Helvetia, Medan Helvetia, Medan City, North Sumatra 20124, Indonesia

detail_description: Vihara Gunung Timur is a serene and spiritually enriching Buddhist temple complex located in Berastagi, Medan. Dating back to the 1960s, this active Taoist and Buddhist temple offers a tranquil atmosphere for inner contemplation amidst lush natural surroundings. The ornate carvings and beautiful statues imported from Myanmar add to the spiritual ambiance of the place.
name: Vihara Gunung Timur
address: Jl. Hang Tuah No.16, Madras Hulu, Medan Polonia, Medan City, North Sumatra 20151, Indonesia

excerpt: Low-key park & gardens featuring ponds, picnic areas, sports facilities & playgrounds.
detail_description: Taman Cadika Pramuka is a serene park and garden offering a range of amenities such as ponds, picnic spots, sports facilities, and playgrounds. The park boasts a well-designed layout with two picturesque bridges crossing over the ponds and ample seating areas to enjoy the tranquil surroundings. Visitors can relish the peaceful atmosphere while taking leisurely strolls or enjoying the gentle breeze by the pool. Additionally, it offers various recreational activities including jogging tracks, basketball courts, and even horse riding facilities.
name: Taman Cadika Pramuka
address: Pangkalan Masyhur, Medan Johor, Medan City, North Sumatra, Indonesia

detail_description: The Tjong Yong Hian Gallery, a private resting place for Tjong Yong Hian and his wife, is an important historical landmark in Medan. While it is not generally open to the public, some family members may allow visits on occasion. The gallery itself was locked during my visit, but I was able to explore the well-maintained garden and admire the beautiful lily pond.
name: Tjong Yong Hian Gallery
address: HMP9+GJG, Jl. Kejaksaan, Petisah Tengah, Medan Petisah, Medan City, North Sumatra 20151, Indonesia

excerpt: This long-running, 2-hectare park features thousands of crocodiles, from young to old.
detail_description: The expansive Penangkaran Buaya Asam Kumbang, a vast 2-hectare park, boasts an impressive collection of numerous crocodiles. With a history dating back to 1959, this Indonesian reptile sanctuary is renowned as the country's largest. The park houses over 2,400 varieties of reptiles and features an artificial lake where these remarkable creatures are nurtured by caretakers.
name: Penangkaran Buaya Asam Kumbang
address: Jl. Bunga Raya II No.8, Asam Kumbang, Medan Selayang, Medan City, North Sumatra 20128, Indonesia

name: Two Colors Sibolangit Waterfall
address: Jl. Sun Yat Sen No.130, Sei Rengas I, Medan Kota, Medan City, North Sumatra 20211, Indonesia

detail_description: Kampoeng Selfie (Kongsi) is a lively and colorful artistic community located in Medan, North Sumatra. It's a popular spot for taking selfies and immersing oneself in the local culture. The area is known for its cleanliness, safety, and friendly residents of all ages. Visitors can expect to find creative alleyways perfect for photo opportunities, making it an ideal destination for those seeking vibrant and picturesque surroundings.
name: Kampoeng Selfie (Kongsi)
address: HMF9+834, Jl. DR. Cipto, Anggrung, Kec. Medan Polonia, Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara 20152, Indonesia

excerpt: Rural artificial lake with small boat rentals, fishing, picnic spots & food vendors.
detail_description: Danau Siombak is a 40-acre rural artificial lake near Medan, popular among locals for its affordable recreational activities. Visitors can rent small boats for leisurely rides on the lake, enjoy fishing, and relax at picnic spots. The area features huts by the lakeside, water ducks, cafes, and live music entertainment.
name: Danau Siombak
address: Jl. Ps. Nippon, Paya Pasir, Medan Marelan, Medan City, North Sumatra 20252, Indonesia

detail_description: Sibolang Durian is a must-visit destination in Medan for durian enthusiasts, offering a delightful open-concept setting that operates around the clock. This charming spot invites you to relax on its benches while indulging in the unique flavors of local durians. Guests can choose their preferred taste profilewhether sweet or slightly bitterand the friendly staff are more than happy to assist with cutting and serving the fruit.
name: Sibolang Durian
address: Jl. Iskandar Muda C-D No.75, Babura, Medan Baru, Medan City, North Sumatra 20152, Indonesia

excerpt: Lively, urban green space with wide, tree-lined paths, outdoor gym equipment & a playground.
detail_description: Taman Ahmad Yani Medan is a vibrant urban oasis that beckons both locals and visitors alike. This central park features expansive, tree-lined pathways perfect for leisurely strolls or invigorating runs. With outdoor gym equipment and a dedicated playground, it caters to fitness enthusiasts of all ages. The park is well-equipped with essential facilities like restrooms, prayer rooms, and ample seating areas, making it an ideal spot for picnics or casual gatherings.
name: Taman Ahmad Yani Medan
address: HMGG+HM6, Jl. Imam Bonjol, J A T I, Medan Maimun, Medan City, North Sumatra 20151, Indonesia

name: Masjid Agung Kota Medan Sumatera Utara
address: Jl. Pangeran Diponegoro, Madras Hulu, Kec. Medan Polonia, Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara, Indonesia

detail_description: Asam Kumbang Crocodile Farm is one of the largest crocodile farms in Indonesia, housing hundreds of these fascinating creatures. Visitors can observe feeding sessions and even take selfies with the crocodiles for a small fee. The farm has undergone renovations to improve and expand its facilities, making it a more spacious and interesting attraction. Despite some dated aspects, it remains an affordable and captivating experience where visitors can witness crocodiles in various enclosures, including large ponds and concrete pools.
name: Asam Kumbang Crocodile Farm
address: Jl. Bunga Raya II No.59, Asam Kumbang, Kec. Medan Selayang, Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara 20128, Indonesia

excerpt: Whimsical water park featuring a lazy tubing river, serpentine slides, big pools & a splash pad.
detail_description: Hairos Water Park is a whimsical aquatic attraction that offers an array of thrilling features. Visitors can enjoy a leisurely tubing river, twisting slides, expansive pools, and an exciting splash pad. This family-friendly destination provides ample opportunities for play and entertainment. However, it should be noted that some rides may be too intense for younger children. Additionally, aside from admission tickets, there are additional costs for slide mats and other amenities.
name: Hairos Water Park
address: Jl. Jamin Ginting No.Km. 14, RW.5, Namo Bintang, Pancur Batu, Deli Serdang Regency, North Sumatra 20353, Indonesia

excerpt: Water park with a lazy river, wave pool, pirate ship, slides, kids' play area & food court.
detail_description: Wonders Water World is an exciting aquatic amusement park that offers a multitude of thrilling attractions for families to enjoy. This remarkable destination features a relaxing gentle current pool, an exhilarating artificial wave pool, an impressive pirate-themed vessel, exciting water slides, and a designated play area for children. Additionally, visitors can find various food options at the conveniently located eating area. Wonders Water World provides the perfect setting for quality family time filled with adventure and entertainment in a safe and enjoyable environment.
name: Wonders Water World
address: HM5G+H89, Komplek CBD Polonia, Jl. Padang Golf, Suka Damai, Medan Polonia, Medan City, North Sumatra 20157, Indonesia

excerpt: Hot springs complex known for its milky blue waters & colorful mineral deposits, plus food stalls.
detail_description: Kawah Putih Dolok Tinggi Raja, also known as Bukit Kapur Tinggi Raja, is a hot springs complex with stunning milky blue waters and vibrant mineral deposits. Located in Dolok Tinggi Raja Village, it's about 90 kilometers from Medan and can be reached by a 3 to 4-hour motorcycle ride through picturesque routes. Visitors are advised to negotiate prices with guides for parking, entry fees, and destination spots.
name: Kawah Putih Dolok Tinggi Raja
address: 4QXP+VJ9, Dolok Marawa, Silau Kahean, Simalungun Regency, North Sumatra 21157, Indonesia

name: Pulau Berhala
address: J867+R2Q, Selat Malaka, Kabupaten Serdang Bedagai, Sumatera Utara, Indonesia

excerpt: Pools, flumes & rubber ring rides down a lazy river, plus fast food outlets with outdoor seating.
detail_description: Wisata Merci is a water park that offers various attractions such as pools, flumes, and rubber ring rides along a lazy river. The facility prioritizes cleanliness and safety, with an abundance of friendly lifeguards present. While the food outlets provide outdoor seating and affordable options, it would be beneficial if prices could be slightly lowered. Additionally, the rental fee for gazebos is considered too high by some visitors.
name: Wisata Merci Waterpark and Resto
address: komp.Medan Resort City, Jl. Perjuangan, Deli Tua, Kec. Namorambe, Kabupaten Deli Serdang, Sumatera Utara 20143, Indonesia

detail_description: Sicike-cike Nature Park is a stunning, secluded destination for nature enthusiasts. Nestled in its original state, this tranquil park offers a serene atmosphere where visitors can unwind and rejuvenate. With its untouched beauty and peaceful ambiance, Sicike-cike is an idyllic spot to immerse oneself in the wonders of nature. However, caution must be exercised when traversing the wooden bridge as it shows signs of decay and can become slippery.
name: "Sicike-cike" Nature Park
address: M92J+R66, Sitinjo, Dairi Regency, North Sumatra 22219, Indonesia

name: Pubbarama Buddhist Centre (PBC)
address: MM96+WWC, Jl. Perak, Kota Bangun, Kec. Medan Deli, Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara 20242, Indonesia

detail_description: Despite its name, the Museum Situs Kota China does not reflect Chinese heritage but rather belongs to Indian (Tamil) culture. Dating back to the 11th Century, Tamils migrated to Medan and established this city known as Cinna Kottai, meaning 'small city'. This historical site offers valuable insights into the past and is a place of great significance.
name: Museum Situs Kotta Cinna
address: PMF4+5PV, Jl. Kota Cina, Paya Pasir, Kec. Medan Marelan, Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara 20254, Indonesia

excerpt: Leafy city park with tennis courts & a jogging track, plus concerts & traditional dance displays.
name: Lapangan Benteng
address: Jl. Pengadilan No.Kel, Petisah Tengah, Medan Petisah, Medan City, North Sumatra 20236, Indonesia

excerpt: Picturesque garden center offering lush greenery & a colorful array of flowers, plus a cafe.
name: The Le Hu Garden
address: Jl. Pendidikan, Deli Tua Barat, Deli Tua, Deli Serdang Regency, North Sumatra 20355, Indonesia

excerpt: Museum containing weapons, medicines & uniforms used in the Indonesian National Revolution.
detail_description: Museum Perjuangan TNI is a historical site that showcases weaponry, medications, and uniforms utilized during the Indonesian National Revolution. It serves as a vivid reminder of Indonesia's struggle against imperialism and its journey towards independence. The museum houses an extensive collection of ancient artifacts, commemorating the nation's past. For history enthusiasts, a visit to this museum is highly recommended. Furthermore, it offers guided tours by military personnel who work at the museum, ensuring a comprehensive understanding of the exhibits.
name: Museum Perjuangan TNI
address: Jl. KH. Zainul Arifin No.8, Petisah Tengah, Medan Petisah, Medan City, North Sumatra 20151, Indonesia

name: Al-Osmani Mosque
address: JL Kol Yos Sudarso, Km. 19, 5, Labuhan, Pekan Labuhan, Kec. Medan Labuhan, Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara 20252, Indonesia

name: Tugu Marga Silalahi
address: RG7H+29V, Jalan Tugu Makam Raja Desa, Silalahi III, Silahisabungan, Dairi Regency, North Sumatra 22284, Indonesia

detail_description: Monumen Guru Patimpus is a significant landmark in Medan, commemorating the city's founder, Guru Patimpus Sembiring Pelawi. Situated at the confluence of Deli River and Babura River, it marks the original village location where he named it Kampung Medan Putri. The monument symbolizes Medan's origin and identity. Located at a strategic intersection in the heart of the city, it is easily accessible to both residents and tourists.
name: Monumen Guru Patimpus Sembiring Pelawi
address: HMRC+HCG, Petisah Tengah, Kec. Medan Petisah, Kota Medan, Sumatera Utara, Indonesia
